config.text:
Welcome to the WATERS GeoViewer


First time users are encouraged to review the brief tutorial to become familiar with the WATERS GeoViewers layout and capabilities.


If youre more adventurous, start by expanding the Operational Layers menu on the left by clicking on the arrow icon next to the Feature Layers item underneath. The Operational Layers menu is where you select which feature layers to display on the map. Note that in order to display a specific layer that all parent layers above it must also be selected. All feature layers selected for display and their symbology, can be viewed by clicking on the Legend control on the right side of the map menu bar ( ). All six of the map controls found there, open menus that can be scrolled up to maximize the map area by clicking on their double arrow icon (  ).


Users are welcome to Contact Us to ask a question, provide feedback, or report a problem.
WATERS GeoViewer 3.0

toolInfo.name: DelineateUsingStartingPoint
toolInfo.description: The Drainage Area Delineation using Starting Point geoprocessing tool is provided for use with the ArcGIS Online Geoprocessing Widget. The tool abstracts the interface of the WATERS Navigation Delineation service for simplified usage within ArcGIS Online. To see the tool in action visit the EPA WATERS GeoViewer.

parameters.name: StreamSelectionType
parameters.description: Enter a keyword indicating the type of network search requested:Upstream with TributariesUpstream Mainline onlyDownstream with DivergencesDownstream Mainline onlyTo learn more about searching the NHDPlus network, visit the NHDPlus v2.1 User Guide and reference the section entitled Understanding and Using NHDPlusV2 and specifically the subsection entitled NHDPlus and Divergences for an explanation and illustrations of the main and minor paths associated with divergences.

parameters.name: StartingPoint
parameters.description: Enter a start point as a feature class complex object. May be any valid simple point feature class the server can access. The point will be snapped to nearest NHDPlus flowline for use in drainage area delineation.

parameters.name: MaxDistanceKm
parameters.description: The distance in kilometers at which to restrict the network search.

parameters.name: MaxFlowtimeDay

toolInfo.name: SearchUsingStartingPoint
toolInfo.description: Service to discover EPA Office of Water linked program data.

parameters.name: StreamSelectionType
parameters.description: Navigation methodology for network discovery of linked data.

parameters.name: StartingPoint
parameters.description: Coordinate location to be indexed to the appropriate NHDPlus flowline from which to begin the navigation.

parameters.name: MaxDistanceKm
parameters.description: Distance in kilometers to limit navigation. If MaxDistanceKm or MaxFlowTimeDay is not provided the full extent of the navigation will be returned. For certain configurations in large networks this is likely to timeout or otherwise fail to return results.

parameters.name: MaxFlowtimeDay
parameters.description: Flow time in days to limit navigation. If MaxDistanceKm or MaxFlowTimeDay is not provided the full extent of the navigation will be returned. For certain configurations in large networks this is likely to timeout or otherwise fail to return results.

config.text:
First time users are encouraged to review the brief tutorial to become familiar with the WATERS GeoViewers layout and capabilities.


The EPA Office of Waters Watershed Assessment, Tracking and Environmental Results System (WATERS) integrates water-related information by linking it to the NHDPlus stream network. The National Hydrography Dataset Plus (NHDPlus) provides the underlying geospatial hydrologic framework that supports a variety of network-based capabilities, including upstream/downstream search and watershed delineation. The WATERS GeoViewer provides easy access to these data and capabilities via the Internet on any desktop or mobile device. In doing so, it implements the concepts and principles of the Open Water Data Initiative, including the Network Linked Data Index.


Users are welcome to Contact Us to ask a question, provide feedback, or report a problem.


To sign into ArcGIS Online or change your current ArcGIS Online affiliation, visit the WATERS GeoViewer item information page.
